Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.90,0:00:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提高退休年齡\NRaising the age of retirement
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.69,0:00:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是對美國夢不可容忍的侵蝕\Nis an unacceptable erosion of the American Dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.08,0:00:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果共和黨無法通過福利改革\NIf the Republicans fail to pass a reasonable Omnibus package
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.53,0:00:17.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,達成合理的綜合解決方案\Nby demanding entitlement reform,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.97,0:00:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就會迫使聯邦政府凍結開銷\Nthey will force the federal government into a spending freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.19,0:00:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凍瘡會長在他們手上  不是我們手上\NThe frostbite will be on their hands. Not ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.34,0:00:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這句是不是有點過了  凍瘡那句\NDo you think that's a bit much? The frostbite bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.33,0:00:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是國情咨文  先生\NWell, it's the State of the Union, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.91,0:00:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們想爭取中部各州的支持\NWe want to appeal to the flyover states.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.54,0:00:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們會喜歡那句話的\NThey'll like that line.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.09,0:00:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想要點更有力的句子\NI want something more forceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.57,0:00:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們手上沾滿血\NBlood on their hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.81,0:00:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不行\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.66,0:00:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把我們丟回冰河紀\NThrow us back into the ice age.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.33,0:00:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜歡那句  克裏斯蒂娜  我們試試\NI like that, Christina. Let's try that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.36,0:00:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琳達  克裏斯蒂娜  你也過來\NLinda. Christina, you come up here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.39,0:00:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,世上有兩種副總統\NThere are two types of vice presidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.41,0:00:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,受氣包和鬥牛士\NDoormats and matadors.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.48,0:00:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得我想做哪種呢\NWhich do you think I intend to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.17,0:01:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德\NRaymond.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.83,0:01:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在為內政操心\NHe's hung up on the domestic agenda.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.78,0:01:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一句關於中國的話也沒說\NNot a single word about China.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.51,0:01:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的直覺是對的\NHis instincts are right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.80,0:01:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果政府在演講後第二天關門\NIf the government shuts down one day after the speech,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.96,0:01:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他講了什麼就完全不重要了\Nnot a single word in the speech matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.51,0:01:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們得馬上解決凍結開銷的問題\NWe have to address the freeze now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.59,0:01:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中國的事得靠後\NChina comes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.92,0:01:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,兩黨為了改革的事吵了幾個月了\NBoth parties have been wrangling over entitlements for months.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.36,0:01:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,未來三天裏\NWhat makes you think a miracle
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.66,0:01:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎麼可能出現奇跡\Nis gonna happen in the next three days?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.10,0:01:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們給共和黨他們想要的\NWe give the Republicans exactly what they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.11,0:01:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,退休年齡\NRetirement age?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.22,0:01:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.08,0:01:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是不可跨越的界限\NThat's a line in the sand we cannot cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.68,0:01:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們最終還是得跨  所以何必爭下去呢\NWe will cross it eventually, so why keep fighting it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.41,0:01:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以推動參議院通過法案\NI can push this through the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.91,0:01:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一旦我做到  總統就能在國情咨文中\NAnd once I do, the president will announce
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.08,0:01:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宣佈兩黨達成了一項重要協議\Na major bipartisan agreement in the State of the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.37,0:01:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們避免了政府關門\NWe avoid a government shutdown,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.99,0:01:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而功勞歸白宮\Nand the White House gets credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.36,0:01:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太冒險了\NIt's a huge risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.75,0:01:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一旦失敗  會顏面掃地\NAnd if it fails, a huge embarrassment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.50,0:01:56.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那也是丟我的臉\NThe embarrassment will be entirely my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.63,0:01:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這事我來擔\NThis is on my shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.51,0:02:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使如此  也不好說服總統\NEven so, the president is gonna require some serious persuasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.15,0:02:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我去跟他談\NI'm happy to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.12,0:02:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別  我來吧\NNo. No. I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.45,0:02:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,朋友去說  他更容易接受\NHe'll be more amenable if it comes from a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.10,0:02:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒錯  可信的密友\NYou're right. A trusted confidant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.59,0:02:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我去試試水吧\NLet me test the waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.61,0:02:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塔斯克黨  成員  一人\NThe Cult of Tusk. Membership: one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.52,0:02:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不過那個信徒恰好是\NBut that one disciple just so happens to be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.79,0:02:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自由世界最有權力的人\Nthe most powerful man in the free world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.94,0:02:32.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至少目前還是\NFor now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.34,0:04:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,福利改革  把退休年齡提到67歲\NThe entitlements. Raising the age of eligibility to 67.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.69,0:04:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們那邊不會同意的\NYour people will never go for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.03,0:04:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,領導層同意  他們就會點頭\NThey will if the leadership does.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.85,0:04:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而領導層會同意的\NAnd the leadership will.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.21,0:04:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我還沒斷奶時這事就是兩黨的爭議焦點\NThey fought us on this since I was in diapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.06,0:04:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,假如我能說服我黨同意提高退休年齡\NAssuming that I can get this past my people and convince them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.42,0:04:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能說服你那邊嗎\Ncan you convince yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.41,0:04:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這很困難\NIt's a tough sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.73,0:04:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是參議院多數黨領袖  赫克特\NYou're the Senate majority leader, Hector.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.20,0:04:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不需要遊說  可以直接命令\NYou don't have to sell. You can dictate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.97,0:04:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想要什麼回報\NWhat do you want in return?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.32,0:04:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一個正常運轉的政府  避免開銷凍結\NA working government. We stave off the freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.53,0:04:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在《教育法案》上贏了\NYou won on education.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.84,0:04:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們讓你當上了副總統\NWe confirmed you as vice president.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.15,0:04:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,共和黨需要贏一次  弗蘭克\NThe Republicans need a win, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.74,0:04:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就是在提供贏的機會\NAnd that's what I'm offering.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.31,0:04:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們在福利改革上贏了\NYou get a win on entitlements.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.81,0:04:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們避免了關門\NWe avoid a shutdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,兩黨合作  雙方都得分\NEveryone gets points for bipartisanship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.52,0:04:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我擔心誰\NYou know who I'm worried about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.00,0:04:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯蒂斯·哈斯\NCurtis Haas.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.60,0:04:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是個麻煩  弗蘭克\NHe's a troublemaker, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.71,0:04:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還控制了你三分之一的黨內成員\NWho controls a third of your caucus.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.26,0:04:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他絕不會同意的\NAnd he'll never go for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.98,0:04:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他就想看民主黨不好過\NHe wants to see the Democrats suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.97,0:04:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓他考慮一下\NJust bring him to the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.79,0:05:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只求這個\NThat's all I'm asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.30,0:05:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蓋拉格小姐  我叫盧卡斯·古德溫\NMiss Gallagher? My name is Lucas Goodwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是《華盛頓先驅報》的副主編\NI'm a deputy editor at the Washington Herald.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.46,0:05:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,古德溫先生  拜託了\NMr. Goodwin, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.58,0:05:16.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只需要幾分鐘  我不求別的\NJust a few moments. That's all I'm asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.07,0:05:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我想跟你說話  就會回你的電話\NIf I wanted to talk to you, I would have returned your calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.33,0:05:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你讀過我的郵件嗎\NDid you read my emails?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.64,0:05:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讀了  所以我沒聯繫你\NYes. Which is why I didn't call.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.81,0:05:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請給我個機會解釋\NGive me a chance to walk you through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.34,0:05:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得趕回白宮\NI have to get back to the White House.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.50,0:05:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-抱歉  -彼得·羅素是被殺害的\N- I'm sorry. - Peter Russo was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放手\NLet go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.09,0:05:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,佐伊·巴恩斯也是  我跟她是同事\NSo was Zoe Barnes. I was working with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.79,0:05:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,住口  聽我說...\NStop and listen --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.61,0:05:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗蘭克·安德伍德是幕後黑手\NFrank Underwood is the one who did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.84,0:05:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聽著  這是一派胡言\NListen! This is nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.50,0:05:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,酒駕記錄  聽證會  所有都是...\NThe DUI. The brack hearing. All of it was part of --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.95,0:05:35.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能再這樣了  好嗎\NThis has to stop. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.25,0:05:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安德伍德找過你了嗎\NDid Underwood talk to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.55,0:05:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-讓你不要和別人說這些事嗎  -沒有\N- Tell you not to speak with anybody? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.39,0:05:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,道格·斯坦普嗎\NDoug Stamper?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.99,0:05:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,無論你以為發生了什麼\NWhatever you think happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.23,0:05:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,無論是什麼讓你這樣跟蹤我...\Nwhatever compelled you to stalk me like this --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.15,0:05:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是唯一可能知道點什麼的人\NYou're the only person who might know something,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.02,0:05:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能理解得了的人\Nwho could understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.95,0:05:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我沒有別人可以說這事了\NI've got -- I've got no one else I can talk --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.52,0:05:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不理解  也不想理解\NI don't understand. And I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.91,0:05:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,行嗎  這裏面沒什麼內情\NOkay? There's no story here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.62,0:05:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜託了  只要五分鐘\NPlease, just five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.92,0:05:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想想你自己的行為\NJust think about what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.76,0:05:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,守在樓外\NWaiting outside of a building --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.67,0:05:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果不是弗蘭克·安德伍德  彼得可能還活著\NPeter would still be alive if it wasn't for Frank Underwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.53,0:06:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我花了很大力氣忘記彼得的事\NI've worked really hard to put Peter behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.75,0:06:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我再看到你  你再來找我\NSo if I see you again, if I hear from you again,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.51,0:06:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不僅會報警\NI'll not only contact the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.00,0:06:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還會讓副總統知道你在對他說三道四\NI'll let the vice president know what you're saying about him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.96,0:06:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到時候你就等著特勤局找上門來吧\Nand then you can deal with the Secret Service, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.49,0:06:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是正常的海外聲音  中國那邊有些雜音\NIt's the usual overseas chatter. Bit of a bum in China,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.58,0:06:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我們覺得原因在貿易緊張\Nbut we chalk that up to the trade tensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.30,0:06:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特勤局\NSecret Service.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.62,0:06:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統和副總統收到的死亡威脅數正常\NAverage number of death threats to both POTUS and the VP.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.55,0:06:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們都交給了聯調局的好夥伴們\NWe passed them along to our dear friends at the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.25,0:06:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聯調局呢\NFBI?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.52,0:06:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聯調局向我們特勤局的\NThe FBI confirms the level of activity
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.97,0:06:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好夥伴們確認了活動程度\Nof our dear friends at the Secret Service.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.67,0:06:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們全部進行了追蹤調查  沒有高級別的威脅\NWe followed up on everything. No high-level threats.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.72,0:06:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們沒有需要直接\NSo nothing we need to report directly
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.33,0:06:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,向總統和副總統匯報的內容嗎\Nto the president or vice president?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.81,0:06:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-沒有  -謝謝  先生們\N- No. - Thank you, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.58,0:06:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你發的郵件還有別人看過嗎\NThe email you sent. Has anyone else seen it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.12,0:06:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除了告知我的特工外  沒有了\NExcept for the agent that alerted me, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.32,0:06:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他機構可能會偶然看到\NOther agencies might have stumbled upon this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.90,0:06:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使如此  他們大概也不會在意\NEven so, they probably ignored it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.46,0:06:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道是誰發的帖子嗎\NAny idea who's making the posts?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.76,0:06:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,暗網論壇\NDeep Web forums.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.97,0:06:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幾乎無法追蹤  很可能就是一個人\NAlmost impossible to trace. Lone wolf most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.46,0:07:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要你找到這個人\NI want you to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.76,0:07:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,得有對生命構成直接威脅的證據\NWe need a direct threat to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.47,0:07:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,副總統剛剛上任\NThe vice president just assumed office.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.82,0:07:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這類陰謀論絕不能甚囂塵上\NI can't have this conspiracy stuff going mainstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.58,0:07:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-這類傳言一般會漸漸平息  -我不能冒這個險\N- This sort of thing usually fizzles out -- - I can't take the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你去找到這個人  把他關起來\NI want you to find him and put him away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.17,0:07:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他並沒犯罪  -但他有這個傾向\N- He hasn't committed a crime. - But he wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.23,0:07:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就來個推波助瀾\NSo help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.10,0:07:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那要耗費人力\NThat requires manpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.97,0:07:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你手裏有人\NYou've got men.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.12,0:07:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,會暴露我的  道格\NIt exposes me, Doug.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.73,0:07:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直給你透露消息  因為你是老朋友了\NI've always kept you informed because you're an old pal
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.83,0:07:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我信任你  但...\Nand I trust you. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.63,0:07:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你這是要我展開正式行動\NWe're talking about an operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.38,0:07:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是你在白宮工作的老朋友\NI'm an old pal who now works at the White House.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.47,0:07:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老朋友之間說說\NBetween old pals,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.91,0:07:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我這個行政部門聯絡官已經當得太久了\NI've been stuck as the executive liaison for way too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.29,0:07:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您是否擔心\NHow worried are you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.86,0:07:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您所在社區的學校內會發生大規模槍擊事件\Nthat a mass shooting could happen in a school in your community?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.58,0:07:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常擔心  比較擔心  不怎麼擔心\NGreat deal, somewhat, not so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.95,0:07:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,完全不擔心  還是不確定\Nnot at all, unsure?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.14,0:07:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的聲音很性感嘛  人怎麼樣\NYou sound hot. Are you hot?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.93,0:08:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生\NSir...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.61,0:08:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比較性感  非常性感\NSomewhat hot? A great deal hot?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這裏是林奇堡兒童醫院小兒科\NLynchburg Children's, Pediatric Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.82,0:08:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我找謝莉爾·波斯納\NCan I talk to Cheryl Posner?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.91,0:08:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  她正在值班\NSorry. She's on duty right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.39,0:08:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是她女兒\NIt's her daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.76,0:08:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請稍候\NHold on one moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.89,0:09:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞秋  瑞秋嗎\NRachel? Rachel?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.89,0:09:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甜心  你在聽嗎  請別...\NSweetheart, are you there? Please, do--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.26,0:09:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您好\NHello?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.36,0:09:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您好  傑伊先生\NHello, Mr. Jay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.00,0:09:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我叫瑞秋\NMy name is Rachel
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.70,0:09:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,代表全國槍支教育中心向您致電\Nand I'm calling on behalf of the National Firearm Education Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.77,0:09:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您能和我簡單聊聊\NWould you be able to speak with me briefly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.09,0:09:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您對槍支立法和第二修正案的看法嗎\Nregarding firearm legislation and Second Amendment legislation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.45,0:09:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就是薇拉力薦的人\NSo, you're Willa's top choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.54,0:09:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我丈夫和我為什麼要選擇你呢\NWhy should you be my husband's and my top choice?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.33,0:09:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在過去十年中\NOver the past 10 years
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.40,0:09:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,關於你們夫婦的報道加起來還不到\Nthe two of you combined have gotten less coverage
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.74,0:09:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,內布拉斯加州資淺眾議員的平均水平\Nthan the average junior congressman from Nebraska.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.01,0:09:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不想太受矚目\NWell, we don't seek the spotlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.44,0:09:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是說你們非要如此\NI'm not suggesting you should.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.41,0:09:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果我沒猜錯\NBut am I correct in assuming
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.84,0:09:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您丈夫會是一位行事積極的副總統\Nthat your husband will be an active vice president?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.49,0:09:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想讓媒體不去關注積極的副總統是比較難的\NIt's harder to keep an active VP out of the press than in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.00,0:09:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我們可以讓媒體剛好有些料可追\Nbut it's possible if we give the media just enough
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.68,0:09:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不至於什麼都拿不到\Nto keep them from starving.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.44,0:09:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在哪長大的  康納\NWhere'd you grow up, Connor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.21,0:09:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,德州  和您一樣\NTexas. Just like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.48,0:09:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,達拉斯嗎\NDallas?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.56,0:10:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拉布克\NLubbock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.60,0:10:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想改口音可比你們難多了\NI had a much thicker accent to get rid of you than y'all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.57,0:10:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎麼知道我有口音\NHow do you know I had one?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.97,0:10:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你倆第一次共同接受採訪\NYour first joint interview,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.21,0:10:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,86年您丈夫競選州議員時\Nwhen your husband was running for state assembly in '86.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.57,0:10:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,網上有嗎\NThat's on the internet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.78,0:10:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有  我聯繫了格林維爾當地的電視台\NNo. No. I contacted the local affiliate in Greenville.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.92,0:10:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們不願郵寄錄像帶\NThey wouldn't send me the tapes via mail,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.34,0:10:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就親自去資料庫看了\Nso I went down there and watched in their vault.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.02,0:10:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跑到南卡羅萊納嗎\NTo South Carolina?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,應聘就得做好準備工作\NWhen I want a job, I do my homework.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.55,0:10:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很期待你的表現\NI look forward to seeing what you come up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.50,0:10:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝  安德伍德夫人\NThank you, Mrs. Underwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.73,0:10:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,週四見\NThursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.48,0:10:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這怎麼能算勝利\NI don't see how this is a victory for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.52,0:10:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們要麼面臨開銷凍結\NOur choices are the freeze,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.21,0:10:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,民主黨會為這個飽受責難\Nwhich the Democrats get blamed for, or --
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.99,0:10:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不一定  共和...\NNot necessarily. The Republi--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.71,0:10:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們也一樣會受責難\NNo, which we definitely get blamed for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.18,0:10:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-要麼給他們  -福利改革嗎  弗蘭克\N- Or we offer them -- - Entitlements, Frank?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.88,0:11:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們已經表了態  不能回頭了\NWe took a stand. We can't turn back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.66,0:11:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我寧可讓政府停轉\NI'd rather see the government grind to a halt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.65,0:11:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果頭條是\NThink of the headline:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.04,0:11:07.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,《民主黨高層通過法案  避免開銷凍結》\N"Democrat Leadership Enacts Entitlement Reform, Staves Off Freeze."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.58,0:11:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是團結和進步的表現\NWe show unity. We offer progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.26,0:11:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們說服幾個中堅保守派吧\NLet's convert some lifelong conservatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.89,0:11:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,門多薩答應合作了嗎\NYou have Mendoza's assurance he'll work with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.80,0:11:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\NI do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.49,0:11:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可不想把頭伸出去\NI don't want to put our necks out there
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.45,0:11:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等人家落刀\Njust to have the guillotine fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.71,0:11:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不會的  我也會一起伸出去\NYou won't. My neck will be right out there with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.37,0:11:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗蘭西斯暈血\NFrancis faints at the sight of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.35,0:11:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,絕不會允許他們割傷他的皮膚\NHe'd never let them break the skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.63,0:11:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,敬團結\NTo unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.99,0:11:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不不不  別這樣\NNo, no, no, no, no. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.78,0:12:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拉瑞  能來一趟嗎\NLarry, can you come by?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.45,0:12:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我電腦不知道怎麼了\NSomething weird's going on with my computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.82,0:12:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.40,0:12:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別這樣\NCome on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.93,0:12:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎麼回事\NHey, what's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.95,0:12:35.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒事  我修好了\NNothing. It's fine. Uh, I fixed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.35,0:12:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\NOkay. Cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.95,0:12:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還不夠革新\NIt's not as progressive as I'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.66,0:12:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不夠極端吧\NYou mean radical.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.58,0:13:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,退休年齡升到67歲  2055年前政府都能負擔福利\NRaising retirement age to 67 makes entitlements solvent until 2055.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.40,0:13:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還能省一萬億\NAnd it saves us over a trillion dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.75,0:13:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不花納稅人的錢\Nwithout a single penny of taxpayer income.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.77,0:13:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,改到68歲能再省三千億\N68 would give us another 300 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.79,0:13:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我還想禁止提前退休\NAnd I'd like to eliminate early retirement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.51,0:13:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,完全禁止嗎\NEntirely?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.26,0:13:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不可能\NForget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.23,0:13:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,68歲退  64歲早退呢\NWhat about 68 and 64?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.56,0:13:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要對選民負責\NI have a responsibility to my constituents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.81,0:13:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我承諾過某些問題絕不妥協\NI promised I wouldn't waver when it comes to things --
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.01,0:13:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,難道要讓茶黨決定財政立法嗎\NAre we really going to allow the Tea Party to determine fiscal legislation?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.01,0:13:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}民共兩黨票數僵持時  茶黨的傾向能決定局勢
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.82,0:13:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我從沒指望他們幫忙\NI've never been beholden to the Tea Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.60,0:13:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,得了吧  柯蒂斯\NCome on, Curtis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.62,0:13:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有茶黨政治行動委員會\NYou wouldn't have won reelection
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.69,0:13:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,給你的一千萬  你也贏不了重選\Nif their PACs hadn't dumped 10 million into your campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.62,0:13:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他們對縮減開支的看法\NIf their definition of budgetary conservatism
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.82,0:13:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,與我不謀而合  那就正好...\Nhappens to overlap with mine, that's a function--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.21,0:13:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯蒂斯  柯蒂斯  友善一點\NCurtis. Curtis. Let's show some goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.51,0:13:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,68歲和64歲可以接受嗎\NCan you stomach 68 and 64?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.65,0:13:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馬上生效嗎\NEffective immediately?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.81,0:13:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,五年以後\NFive years from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.71,0:13:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒興趣\NNot interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.50,0:13:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不能突然拋出這個提議\NWell, you know we can't throw this on people without any warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.43,0:13:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,得給他們時間消化\NThey need some time to digest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.13,0:13:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對不起  就是不行\NI'm sorry. I just can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.66,0:13:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  回去跟你們的幕僚和同事商量一下\NOkay. Meet with your staff. Consult with your colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.49,0:13:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也回去商量  明天再談\NI'll consult with mine. And let's talk tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.53,0:13:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  沒問題\NAll right. I can agree to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.20,0:14:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這第一步很不錯\NBut this is a good first step.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.04,0:14:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,修正案通過後  法案進行表決時\NHow do we make sure Curtis can't filibuster
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.51,0:14:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯蒂斯阻撓議事怎麼辦\Nwhen we get the amendment passed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.96,0:14:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果能走到那步\NAssuming we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.96,0:14:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只跟你說  我覺得我們可以改變他的想法\NBetween you and me, I'm sure we can turn him around.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.85,0:14:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是不想冒險\NI just want to be on the safe side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.73,0:14:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們讓修正案的表決\NWe make sure the passage of the amendment
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.30,0:14:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成為法案表決的一部分\Nconstitutes the passage of the bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.86,0:14:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事先約定\NBy previous agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.84,0:14:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒錯  修正案一通過\NYeah, that's right. We pass the amendment,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.22,0:14:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就完事了\Nand then we're done. Wham, bam.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.50,0:14:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能落到紙上嗎\NCan we put that in writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.93,0:14:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓艾瑞克森找我吧\NHave Erikson reach out to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.14,0:14:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常感謝\NMuchos gracias.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.15,0:14:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,慢用\NThere you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.42,0:14:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盧卡斯·古德溫\NLucas Goodwin?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.32,0:15:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,晚上好  盧卡斯\NGood evening, Lucas.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.95,0:15:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對著麥克風說話\NSpeak into the microphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.12,0:15:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是誰\NWho are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.87,0:15:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,返回主屏  打開另一個應用\NGo to the home screen. Open the other app.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.54,0:15:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先告訴我你是誰\NTell me who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.53,0:15:54.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你調查過我  想必已經知道我是誰了\NYou've done your research. You know who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.28,0:15:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我怎麼知道那是不是你的真實身份\NI -- I know who you claim to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.14,0:16:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要是現在還不相信我  那就不必談了\NAnd if you're not convinced by now, goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.13,0:16:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別別\NWait.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.06,0:16:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聽你的  我返回主屏了\NAll right, I'm on the home screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.67,0:16:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打開驗證程序\NOpen the notary app.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.38,0:16:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是什麼\NWhat is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.66,0:16:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,確保你不為執法部門工作\NTo ensure you aren't law enforcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.94,0:16:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是\NI'm -- I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.41,0:16:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就簽了它\NThen sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.58,0:16:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎麼簽\NHow?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.64,0:16:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把你的拇指按在攝像頭上  然後點"掃瞄"\NHold your thumb to the camera and press "Capture."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.55,0:16:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,萬一你是執法部門的呢\NHow do I know you're not law enforcement?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.65,0:16:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要麼簽了這文件  要麼走人\NSign the document or walk away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.94,0:16:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了  我簽好了\NAll right. I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.73,0:16:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,點"發送"\NPress "Send."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.57,0:16:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,發送到哪\NWhere is this going?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.78,0:16:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我用了伊朗和其他12個國家的代理\NI'm VPNing through Iran and 12 other countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.71,0:16:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不用擔心  鏈接很安全\NDon't worry. It's secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.47,0:16:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最後一件事\NNow, one last thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.24,0:16:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要《華盛頓先驅報》\NI need the two-step verification code
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.54,0:16:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,內部服務器的兩步驗證碼\Nfor the Herald's internal servers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.51,0:17:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我根本不知道該怎麼做\NI -- I don't -- I don't even know how to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.94,0:17:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你當然知道  看你的郵箱\NYes, you do. Check your email.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.55,0:17:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把這平板毀了  尤其要把產品序列號抹乾淨\NDestroy the iPad, especially the serial number
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.95,0:17:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,郵件記牢之後就刪掉\Nand delete the email after you've memorized it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.44,0:17:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祝你好運\NGood luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還在嗎\NHello?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.44,0:17:31.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德  還在聽嗎\NRaymond, are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.40,0:17:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.82,0:17:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  弗蘭克  我還以為看到了一隻印加地鳩\NSorry, Frank. I -- I thought I saw an Inca dove.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.19,0:17:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肯定是冬遷飛錯方向了\NMust have flown the wrong direction for winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.57,0:17:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你那邊好像風挺大  你在哪呢\NIt sounds windy. Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.60,0:17:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我家樓頂  裝了個野鳥餵食器\NTop of my building. Got a bird feeder up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.18,0:17:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統的工作做得不錯  聽說他同意了\NNice work with the President. I hear we have a green light.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.27,0:17:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他一開始也不願意  但還是讓步了\NHe pushed back in the beginning, but yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.90,0:17:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的寫手正在改講稿\NHis writers are reworking the speech now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.04,0:18:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我這邊也快成了  五年後  68退休  64早退\NI'm very close to a deal.  68/64 in five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.72,0:18:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,按說好的削減開支\NSpending cuts as discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.47,0:18:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,說定了嗎\NIs that rock solid?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.86,0:18:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就差握手簽字了\NSoon as we shake hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.06,0:18:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是誰在作梗\NWhat's the hold-up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.26,0:18:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯蒂斯·哈斯  不過也在意料之中\NCurtis Haas, which isn't a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.34,0:18:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我過會兒就和他見面  他是最後的障礙了\NI'm meeting with him soon. He's the final hurdle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.27,0:18:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,時間掐得太正好了  弗蘭克\NCutting it pretty close, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.69,0:18:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這可是歷史性的時刻\NWell, this is -- this is historic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.52,0:18:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,約翰遜當總統時共和黨人就想推動福利改革了\NThe Republicans have wanted entitlement reform since Johnson.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.21,0:18:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯蒂斯會同意的\NCurtis will come around.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.36,0:18:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另外我們得在講稿裏提到延遲退休的事\NIn the meantime we should get the new retirement age into the speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.28,0:18:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看還是別說得太詳細  弗蘭克\NI would stay away from the specifics, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.53,0:18:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就算參議院通過了  眾議院沒準也...\NI mean, I-- even if it passes, the House might--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.92,0:18:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我對眾議院的瞭解\NI know the House better
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.84,0:18:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比你對鳥深入得多  雷蒙德\Nthan you know birds, Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.58,0:18:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相信我  他們肯定會通過參議院的版本\NBelieve me when I say they'll pass the Senate version.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.09,0:18:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我去跟總統說說\NI'll talk to the President.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.18,0:18:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但這事絕不能有差錯\NJust make sure this is airtight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.74,0:18:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多謝你  什麼事\NThank you. What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.27,0:18:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盧卡斯·古德溫\NLucas Goodwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.44,0:18:47.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,《先驅報》的那個\NFrom the Herald.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.49,0:18:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他肯定在和佐伊一起調查\NHe must have been working with Zoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.36,0:18:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他知道多少\NHow much does he know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.80,0:18:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不會比她多\NNo more than she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.00,0:18:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她知道的可不少\NShe knew enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.41,0:18:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在辦  先生\NI'm on it, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.67,0:18:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有證據嗎\NProof?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.96,0:18:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還沒有\NNot yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.75,0:18:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎麼搞的  道格\NJesus, Doug.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.38,0:19:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,局面在控制中  我只是想告訴你一聲\NIt's under control. I just thought you should be aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.52,0:19:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在跟總統  共和黨和塔斯克周旋\NI'm juggling the President, the Republicans, Tusk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.71,0:19:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我不能...  -你就繼續忙你的\N- I can't -- - And you should stay focused on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.33,0:19:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,古德溫交給我處理  你無須擔心\NGoodwin's on my plate. Not yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.85,0:19:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一直到20世紀\NIt wasn't until the 20th century
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.79,0:19:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,客觀主義理念才成為主流觀念\Nthat the notion of noble objectivism came into the forefront.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.62,0:19:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但事實就是事實\NBut facts are facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.25,0:19:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1992年  事實  有人拿出一張\N1992. Fact: George Bush, Sr.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.29,0:19:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老布什詢問售貨掃瞄機是如何工作的照片\Nis shown asking how a grocery scanner works,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.20,0:19:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,進而攻擊他無知\Nand he gets nailed for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.22,0:19:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真相是  他們向他展示的是一個新模型機\NFact? They were showing him a new model.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.23,0:19:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他只是在問新機器與舊機器的差別\NHe was asking how the new one was different than the old one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.81,0:19:35.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好奇而已  並非無知\NCuriosity, not ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.60,0:19:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但語境的缺失卻傳達了一個更有衝擊力的觀點\NBut the lack of context told a more powerful narrative.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.73,0:19:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在對事實的諸多整理中\NThere is no arrangement of facts
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.03,0:19:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有哪個是...完全客觀的\Nthat is, uh, purely objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.90,0:19:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們總算可以做點什麼了  終於有手段了\NWe can finally do something. We have the means to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.46,0:19:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪個毛都沒長全的少年黑客...\NSome teenage pimple-faced hacker --
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.30,0:19:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是很高端的入侵\NThis was a sophisticated infiltration.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.03,0:19:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是小孩子做得出來的\NIt's not the work of a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.47,0:19:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看  郵件在這裏\NLook. Here's the email.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.43,0:19:57.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,機器人希羅尼穆斯\NHieronymus Bot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.43,0:19:57.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}希羅尼穆斯  古希臘史學家  以公正著名
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.65,0:19:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聯調局已經追捕他很多年了\NThe FBI's been hunting him for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.85,0:20:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盧卡斯  聽我說\NLucas, listen to me --
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.43,0:20:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我們拿到了通訊記錄\NIf we get these records,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.40,0:20:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我需要你幫忙理順時間先後\NI'll need your help tracking timelines,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.89,0:20:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拼湊整件事的發展...\Npiecing together the chronology of the --
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.79,0:20:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  你只想找個人安慰你\NNo. You want somebody to hold your hand
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.86,0:20:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告訴你  做這些無用功沒什麼不對\Nand say it's okay to go on this fucking goose chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.51,0:20:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不該在伊薩卡教書  你的能力不止如此\NYou shouldn't be teaching in Ithaca. You're better than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.35,0:20:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你該回華盛頓  -我就該待在這裏\N- You should be back home -- - I belong here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.20,0:20:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對一群宿醉未消的英語專業大學生嘮叨嗎\NDroning on to a bunch of hungover English majors?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.19,0:20:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒錯\NExactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.92,0:20:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你對真相的看法是錯的  客觀事實是存在的\NYou're wrong about the truth. There is objective truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.56,0:20:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他殺了她\NHe killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.77,0:20:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道這是事實\NYou know it's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.12,0:20:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事實就是\NHere's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.03,0:20:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我媽最多只剩10到15年了\NMy mom has 10, 15 years left at best.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我畢業後加起來也沒有上個月跟她相處時間久\NI've seen her more in the past month than since I left for school.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.41,0:20:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這裏更簡單  也很安靜\NIt's simpler here. It's quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.46,0:20:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我需要這樣的環境  她需要我\NI need that. She needs me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.71,0:20:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很抱歉  盧卡斯\NI'm sorry, Lucas.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.69,0:20:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉我那晚做出了那樣的反應\NI'm sorry that night how I reacted.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.53,0:20:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很遺憾你失去了你的女友\NI'm sorry you lost your girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.83,0:20:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很遺憾世界就是這麼操蛋\NI'm sorry the world is this fucked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.11,0:20:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是真心的\NI really am.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.63,0:20:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我幫不了你\NBut I can't help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.78,0:21:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他人在哪裏\NWhere's everyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.25,0:21:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我昨天給你幫了個倒忙\NI did you a disservice yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.22,0:21:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不該在整個領導層面前讓你為難\NWe shouldn't have put you on the spot in front of all the leadership.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.86,0:21:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請坐  柯蒂斯\NHave a seat, Curtis.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.58,0:21:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們知道你必須堅守立場\NWe know that you have an obligation to take a firm stance,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.17,0:21:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但承諾福利改革是你競選的核心\Nbut entitlement reform is something you ran on,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.56,0:21:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在唾手可得了\Nand now it's within your grasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.11,0:21:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,說說你的顧慮吧\NSo tell us your fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.35,0:21:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,顧慮就是民主黨又會贏一把\NThat the Democrats get another win.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.24,0:21:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們在中期選舉中失利\NWe suffer in the midterms,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.49,0:21:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下一屆國會就會廢除協議\Nand the next Congress dismantles the agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.47,0:21:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得我們在玩花招\NYou think we're being disingenuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.18,0:21:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的選民不信任政府\NMy constituents don't trust the administration.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.63,0:21:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能讓他們覺得我們受到了蒙騙\NI can't have them thinking the wool's been pulled over our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.19,0:21:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如我所料  赫克特\NAs I suspected. Hector?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.16,0:21:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗蘭克和我建議\NFrank and I propose this:
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.47,0:22:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們加入一項簡單多數條款\NWe include a super majority point of order
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.04,0:22:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,十年內不再就這個問題進行新的立法討論\Nagainst revisiting the issue for 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.14,0:22:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白紙黑字寫下來\NYou have it in black and white.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.57,0:22:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,達成一項長期的嚴肅承諾  不會被撤銷\NA serious, long-term commitment with no opportunity to dismantle.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.97,0:22:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是加在其他要求之上\NAnd that's on top of everything else we asked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.63,0:22:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,退伍軍人事務管理局和聯邦救災署的經費維持不變\NVA services and FEMA stay at current levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.58,0:22:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他機構的經費削減為你提議的80%到100%\NEverything else at 80 to 100 percent of the cuts you propose.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.21,0:22:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你贏了  柯蒂斯\NYou get your win, Curtis.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.94,0:22:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們只想避免災難\NWe just avoid disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.26,0:22:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也許國家應該見識一下災難\NMaybe the country needs to see what disaster looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.91,0:22:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,茶黨的影響力很大  而你又為他們宣傳\NThe Tea Party has a strong voice, and you're its bullhorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.66,0:22:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓你的選民看到  這份影響力能決定法律\NShow your people that voice can translate into law
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.92,0:22:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不僅僅是激昂的口號\Nand not just add to the noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.70,0:22:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,15年內不得重談  10年不夠\N15 years before revisitation. Not 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.57,0:22:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.26,0:22:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我們通過法案後  眾議院沒有通過\NAnd if the House fails to pass the bill after we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.36,0:22:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你得公開譴責是你們黨造成了這種僵局\Nyou go on record blaming your own party for the gridlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.98,0:22:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們這就算達成協議了\NI believe we have a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.18,0:23:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在聽什麼\NWhat are you listening to?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.29,0:23:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  我關...\NI'm sorry. I'll turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.01,0:23:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別  很好聽  我能聽嗎\NNo, it's nice. Can I listen?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.39,0:23:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的耳朵很乾淨  我保證\NMy ears are clean. I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.93,0:23:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.86,0:23:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-真美  -是啊\N- It's beautiful. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.87,0:23:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好哀傷\NIt's so sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.89,0:23:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能讓我放鬆\NIt helps me relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.18,0:23:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天很辛苦嗎\NLong day?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.92,0:23:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在呼叫中心上班\NI work at a call center.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.29,0:23:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一小時打電話給兩百個陌生人  是挺辛苦\NSo, yeah. 200 strangers an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.59,0:23:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就不打擾你了\NI'll leave you alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.66,0:23:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你大概也不想再和陌生人聊天了\NYou probably don't want to talk to another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.81,0:23:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒關係  你不掛我電話就行\NIt -- it's all right. As long as you don't hang up on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.90,0:23:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你會和他們聊天嗎  那些陌生人\NDo you ever just talk to them? The strangers?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.81,0:24:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不允許\NWe're not allowed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.18,0:24:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,換了我  肯定想問問他們是什麼樣\NAll I would want to do is ask them about who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.71,0:24:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你呢  你做什麼工作\NWhat about you? What do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.78,0:24:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我...在書店和托兒所上班\NI, um, I work at the bookstore and the daycare center.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.09,0:24:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別人第一次給我宣傳冊時\NI had that same look on my face the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.03,0:24:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也是這個表情\Nsomebody handed me one of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.06,0:24:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是...不信教\NYeah, I'm -- I'm just -- I'm not religious.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.37,0:24:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,留著吧  看不看都無所謂\NJust keep it. Check it out, or don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.89,0:24:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們那兒有非常棒的音樂\NWe've got really good music there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.45,0:24:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝你\NI'm -- thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.30,0:24:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,眾議院向參議院提交了一份法案\NThe House sent a bill to the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.25,0:24:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和弗蘭克想給眾議院的那版完全不同\NWhat Frank wants to send back bears zero resemblance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.91,0:24:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為那是兩黨聯合的  不像我們的這份\NBecause it's bipartisan. Unlike ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.96,0:24:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聽著像弗蘭克的話\NThat sounds like something Frank would say.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.62,0:24:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是弗蘭克\NI'm not Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.69,0:24:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是你辦公室的常客\NHe has a desk in your office.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.27,0:24:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果法案在參議院通過\NIf this bill passes in the Senate --
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.94,0:24:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不可能\NIt won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.22,0:25:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們得有所準備  鮑勃\NWe should be prepared, Bob.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.95,0:25:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我就拭目以待了\NWell, I'm prepared to wait and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.24,0:25:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下午愉快  女士們\NHave a good afternoon, ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.61,0:25:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女士們\N"Ladies"?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.67,0:25:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他受到了威脅\NHe's threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.59,0:25:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蠢豬一個\NHe's a pig.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.64,0:25:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,給他點時間\NGive him time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.15,0:25:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以前他身邊有兩個中年白人男子\NHe used to have two white middle-aged guys at his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.36,0:25:21.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在他只能依靠一個黑人和一個小他20歲的女人\NNow he's got a black guy and a woman 20 years his junior.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.20,0:25:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可這女人會開槍\NWho knows how to shoot a rifle.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.94,0:25:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們得繼續勸他\NWe just need to keep at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.15,0:25:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什麼事\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.97,0:25:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凱特琳娜·羅德裏格斯在4號線\NCatalina Rodriguez is on line four.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.08,0:25:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你先下去\NGive me a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.20,0:25:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凱特琳娜\NCatalina.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.26,0:25:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,泰德告訴我是你幹的\NTed told me it was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.55,0:25:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在聽嗎\NYou there?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.15,0:25:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  我在聽\NYes, I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.00,0:25:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,媒體對我們窮追不捨\NThe press won't leave us alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.72,0:25:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們連續幾周跑過來\NFor weeks they're showing up,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.50,0:25:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想拍到我和艾米莉的照片\Ntrying to get pictures of me and Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.72,0:25:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是我洩的密\NIt wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.11,0:25:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有你知情\NYou're the only one who knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.69,0:26:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道事情怎麼會洩露\NI do-- I don't know how the story got out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.73,0:26:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,泰德何必對我撒謊呢\NWhy would Ted lie abut that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.44,0:26:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道  也許他感到羞愧\NI don't know. Maybe -- maybe he's ashamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.69,0:26:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我該怎麼辦  他們什麼時候才會放過我們\NSo what do I do? When will they leave us alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.08,0:26:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不知道  凱特琳娜\NI -- I don't know, Catalina.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.21,0:26:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我受不了這樣的生活\NI can't live like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.87,0:26:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很抱歉  我不知該說什麼\NI'm s-- I'm sorry. I don't know what to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.84,0:26:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾米莉還好嗎\NHow -- how is Emily doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.73,0:26:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凱特琳娜\NCatalina?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.22,0:26:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他自信滿滿\NHe's very confident.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.64,0:26:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他有那個本事嗎\NYeah, but does he have what it takes?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.22,0:26:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等他拿出媒體方案就知道了\NWe'll see when I get his media plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.78,0:26:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他個性如何\NWhat about his personality?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.93,0:26:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迷人  直接  思維縝密\NCharming. Direct. Very thorough.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.70,0:26:54.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他找到了86年我們第一次一起接受採訪的錄像\NHe found our first interview together, in '86.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.47,0:26:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很想重溫一下  他有副本嗎\NI would love to see that. Does he have a copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.27,0:26:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想沒有  電視台只允許他在台裏看\NI don't think so. The TV station made him watch it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.98,0:27:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們該放給總統和第一夫人看\NWe should screen that for the president and the first lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.55,0:27:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓他們學學怎麼接受採訪\NShow 'em how it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.06,0:27:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,克裏斯蒂娜\NChristina...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.80,0:27:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她怎麼了\NWhat about her?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.69,0:27:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有沒有注意到她和總統有什麼不正常\NHave you noticed anything strange between her and the president?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.32,0:27:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什麼意思\NHow do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.75,0:27:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,昨天我在走道裏碰見他們\NI passed them in the hall yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.32,0:27:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們看上去  我說不好  很親密\NAnd they seem -- I don't know -- very intimate.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.16,0:27:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,預備會議上他們是挺熱絡的\NThey did seem cozy at the prep session.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.34,0:27:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得...\NDo you think...?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.44,0:27:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  不一定\NNo. Not necessarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.74,0:27:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不過這想法挺有意思\NAn interesting thought, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.02,0:27:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉打擾  先生\NSorry to interrupt, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.96,0:27:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們在吃午飯\NWe're having lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.03,0:27:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,共和黨人變卦了\NThe Republicans are backing out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.41,0:27:35.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,門多薩的幕僚長給我提了醒\NMendoza's chief of staff just gave me the heads-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.25,0:27:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馬上幫我接門多薩\NGet Mendoza on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.66,0:27:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是柯蒂斯·哈斯  他臨陣退縮了\NIt's Curtis Haas. He got cold feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.15,0:27:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,籠子  差不多像那樣  不過\NCages. It's really kinda like but,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.77,0:27:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但大家會看  挺逗的\Nyou know, people look at 'em. It's kind of fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.20,0:27:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我收到你郵件了\NI got your email.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.06,0:27:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你現在有空嗎\NNow good for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.00,0:27:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,當然  我過會兒打給你\NYeah, sure. Can I call you right back?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.00,0:27:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你究竟想問什麼\NWhat exactly did you need to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.79,0:27:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們在做網絡戰的後續報道\NWe're doing some follow-up pieces on the cyber warfare thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.25,0:27:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就想問問內行人知不知道\NI just wanted to get a layman's understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.23,0:28:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中國人會如何越過防火牆\Nof how the Chinese might get through a firewall.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.14,0:28:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,挺複雜的  不過我可以演示下基本原理\NIt's a bit complicated, but I could show you the basics.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.47,0:28:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那足夠了\NThat's all I need.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.52,0:28:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們使用的是標準多層體系結構\NWe use a standard N-tier architecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.14,0:28:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像多層麵包做成的大三明治\NThink of it like a big sandwich with layers of bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.68,0:28:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每層之間夾著生菜  番茄  烤牛肉之類的\NBetween each is the lettuce, the tomato, the roast beef, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.71,0:28:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我現在輸入的是組織代碼\NWhat I'm pulling up here is the org code,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.41,0:28:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,隔離了數據庫\Nwhich, uh, separates the database --
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.17,0:28:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,該死  我忘了馬上要和銷售部門開會\NShit. I forgot there's a meeting with sales in a couple minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.96,0:28:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想晚點繼續嗎\NYou want to do this later?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.72,0:28:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用  我現在跑過去\NNo. I'll just run over
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.89,0:28:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟他們說我要晚幾分鐘到  馬上回來\Nand let them know I'll be a few minutes late. Be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.00,0:28:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  我就在這兒\NCool. I'll be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.42,0:29:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.97,0:29:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快點快點\NCome on, come on, come on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.35,0:29:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,來了\NThere.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.48,0:29:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快回復啊\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.20,0:29:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.72,0:29:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好勒\NGo.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.87,0:29:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出什麼事了\NSomething wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.09,0:29:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我找不著手機了  真奇怪\NCan't find my phone. It -- it's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.58,0:29:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,剛剛還在的\NI had it just a minute ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.62,0:29:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找到了  不好意思\NHere it is. Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.17,0:29:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒事\NNo problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.47,0:30:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那個多層體系結構\NSo the, uh, N-tier architecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.21,0:30:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我剛說的那個高科技三明治\NThe high-tech sandwich I was talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.81,0:30:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以為門多薩願意合作\NI thought Mendoza was willing to work with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.71,0:30:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是願意  問題在柯蒂斯·哈斯\NHe is. The problem is Curtis Haas.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.79,0:30:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你跟他談過了嗎\NAnd have you spoken with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.36,0:30:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他辦公室不回我們電話\NHis office isn't returning our calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.29,0:30:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,門多薩也是\NNeither is Mendoza's --
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.22,0:30:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不該讓步的\NI should've stuck to my guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.40,0:30:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明天下午才開始投票\NThe vote isn't until tomorrow afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.63,0:30:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一早就會聯繫門多薩\NI'll reach out to Mendoza first thing in the --
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.16,0:30:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這可是國情咨文  弗蘭克\NThis is the State of the Union, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.76,0:30:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能陷入尷尬境地\NI won't be left in limbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.77,0:30:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我們得重寫演講\NIf we need to start rewriting that speech now,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.62,0:30:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一分鐘也不想耽誤\NI don't want to waste a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.14,0:30:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能扭轉局面  先生\NI can turn this around, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.03,0:30:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德告訴我這是你的點子\NYou know, Raymond told me this was your idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.15,0:30:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做出妥協\NTo pursue this compromise.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.86,0:30:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是提出建議\NI suggested it as an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.01,0:30:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他說是你逼他蹚這渾水的\NHe said you bullied him into it,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.63,0:30:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他認為這是個錯誤的決定\Nthat he thought it was a -- a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.15,0:30:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他這麼反對  他就應該勸阻你\NIf he felt so strongly, he should have advised you otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.74,0:30:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德不是政客\NRaymond is not a politician.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.27,0:30:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他依賴於我們的政治意見\NHe relies on our political expertise
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.26,0:30:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正如我們依靠他的商業頭腦\Nas much as we rely on his business acumen.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.33,0:30:53.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或許我們應該到真出現問題再相互指責\NMaybe we shouldn't point fingers until there's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.12,0:30:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你管這不叫問題\NOh, you wouldn't call this a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.55,0:30:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在成為問題之前解決掉就不是問題\NNot if it's solved before it becomes one.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.61,0:31:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要的是個能管理好國會的副總統\NYou see, I wanted a Vice President who can manage Congress.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.05,0:31:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不是個不自量力的人\NNot one who bites off more than he can chew.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.21,0:31:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就相信您做出了正確的決定  先生\NThen have faith you made the right choice, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.43,0:31:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的信念正在迅速地消失殆盡\NWhatever faith I have is quickly evaporating.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.87,0:31:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別給政府丟臉  弗蘭克\NDon't humiliate the administration, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.88,0:31:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也是其中一員了\NYou're part of it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.38,0:31:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是  先生\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.75,0:31:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們談完了\NWe're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.49,0:31:21.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝  總統先生\NThank you, Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.93,0:31:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幫我接內線\NGive me the private line, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.82,0:31:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塔斯克擋我道  古德溫對我窮追不捨\NTusk is blocking my way. Goodwin at my heels.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.11,0:31:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在一步也不能錯\NThere can be no false steps now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.11,0:31:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,越往上爬  爾虞我詐越多\NThe higher up the mountain, the more treacherous the path.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.46,0:31:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盧卡斯·古德溫去找她了\NLucas Goodwin went up to visit her.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.13,0:31:44.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們可能也會來找你\NThey may be looking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.58,0:31:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒人找過我  應該沒人知道我在這兒\NNobody's contacted me. I don't think anyone knows I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.32,0:31:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我們要確保你不會被人發現\NThen we need to make sure it stays that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.62,0:31:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,避免不必要的交談\NDon't speak to anyone you don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.44,0:31:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要去不必要的地方\NDon't go anywhere you don't need to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.85,0:31:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告訴我你聽到我說的了\NTell me you heard what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.02,0:31:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聽到了  我知道了\NI heard you. I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.11,0:32:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我沒事\NI'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.94,0:32:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-敷點冰  -我說了我沒事\N- Put some ice on it. - I said it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.15,0:32:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是什麼\NWhat is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.27,0:32:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你現在還翻我的垃圾嗎\NWhat, are you going through my garbage now?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.56,0:32:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在公交上別人給我的\NSomeone gave it to me on the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.26,0:33:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人聯繫你  就來告訴我\NYou let me know if anyone contacts you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.57,0:33:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉我來晚了\NSorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.69,0:33:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒事\NNo worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.88,0:34:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在你要紋多少\NHow much more you want to do right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.00,0:34:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,填滿這一塊嗎\NFill in this area?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.82,0:34:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯  然後下面再多加一個罌粟\NYeah. And, uh, one more poppy down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.40,0:34:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一次做這麼多啊\NThat's a lot for one sitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.86,0:34:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.35,0:34:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.70,0:34:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗蘭西斯\NFrancis?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.00,0:34:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這就走嗎\NYou're heading in?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.21,0:34:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,門多薩起的早\NMendoza's an early riser.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.42,0:34:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你會解決好的\NYou'll figure this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.04,0:35:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得證明副總統不是吃素的\NI need to prove what the Vice President is capable of.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.58,0:35:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別向他們證明  向我證明\NDon't prove it to them. Prove it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.22,0:35:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯蒂斯抓著我的要害  弗蘭克\NCurtis has me by the tea bags, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.96,0:35:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒他我的黨派就要亂套\NI don't have a working majority without him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.44,0:35:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可他不是多數黨領袖\NHe wasn't elected leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.09,0:35:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是沒錯  但我也得選邊站\NTrue. But I have to pick my battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.10,0:35:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要是在預算問題上無法控制他\NIf you can't control him on budgetary issues --
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.95,0:35:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不光是他  還有聽命於他的15個參議員\NIt's not just him. It's the 15 senators he has under his thumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.95,0:35:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒他們支持我就不能連任\NI won't be the leader next year if they turn on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.80,0:35:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他想我們求他  把他找來\NSo he wants to be courted. Sit him down --
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.62,0:35:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我試過和他談了  但他不肯讓步\NI already tried talking to him. He wouldn't budge.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.68,0:35:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我們一起去跟他談\NThen we'll both talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.80,0:35:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已經表明立場了\NHe's made his position clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.87,0:35:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們都在這張桌子旁握手了\NWe all shook hands at this table.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.06,0:35:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我最多只能保證限制替代修正案\NThe most I can do is put the substitute amendment
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.54,0:35:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,表決前的辯論\Non the floor with limited debate.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.28,0:35:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們那邊公開怎麼說隨你們便\NNow, your people can say whatever they want for the record.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.29,0:35:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我們會投票否決修正案\NBut we're gonna vote the amendment down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.62,0:35:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我對象徵性姿態不敢興趣\NI am not interested in symbolic gestures.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.74,0:35:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只能做到這樣\NThat's all I can offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.95,0:35:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的勇氣哪去了\NWhere's your courage?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.12,0:35:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我權力有限  弗蘭克\NMy power has limits, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.93,0:35:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再有五個共和黨人  你那票就定勝負了\NFive Republicans makes you the deciding vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.93,0:35:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}參議院投票打平時  作為參議院主席的副總統才能投出決定票
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.94,0:35:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在很難說\NNow, it's highly doubtful
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.38,0:35:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們能不能讓他們違反黨派意志投票\Nwe can get them to vote against their own party.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.92,0:35:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他們可以棄權\NBut they might abstain.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.49,0:36:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那需要10人棄權\NYou'd need 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.33,0:36:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,福利改革是共和黨人的長期追求\NEntitlement is the Republicans' white whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.16,0:36:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我至少能說通兩個人\NI can get at least two of 'em to flip.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.76,0:36:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就只需要六票棄權\NAnd you'd only need six abstaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.50,0:36:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾瑞克森已經在打電話了\NErikson's already making calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.81,0:36:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唐納\NDonner?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.57,0:36:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還有普拉斯科\NAnd Pulaski.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.29,0:36:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,給我一份名單  我跟他一起上陣\NAll right. Get me a call list so I can tag-team with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.51,0:36:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在這兒\NGot it right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.48,0:36:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們得使狠招\NWe have to get medieval.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.98,0:36:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要說議院程序\NWhen it comes to parliamentary procedure,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.18,0:36:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有哪條規定我不知道  先生\Nthere's not a rule I don't know, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.69,0:36:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,給我找到能鑽空子的\NFind me the ones we can bend.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.24,0:36:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馬克  你是個明白人\NMark, you're a sensible man.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.85,0:36:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是  我知道  我懂\NYes, I -- I know -- I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.27,0:36:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果  跟你說\NWhat if -- tell you what.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.91,0:36:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你選區內的兩家退伍軍人醫院  對  兩家\NWhat if both VA hospitals in your district -- yes, both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.59,0:36:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別掛  誰\NHold on. Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.05,0:36:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,莫裏亞蒂\NMoriarty.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.66,0:36:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我答應給他的牲牛研究中心撥款\NI promised him an amendment for his bovine research center.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.19,0:36:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這就有六票了\NThat makes six.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.01,0:36:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馬克  如果我能給兩家醫院提供資金\NMark, if I can get you funding for both,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.31,0:36:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你願跟我們合作嗎\Nare you with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.10,0:36:46.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常好\NExcellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.15,0:36:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你這幾天來白宮\NYou come by the White House
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.98,0:36:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟我共進午餐吧\Nand have lunch with me sometime soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.80,0:36:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再見  數目夠了\NBye-bye. We have the numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.90,0:36:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你打斷點名之後\NOnce you break the quorum call
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.42,0:36:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,會有些麻煩\Nit's gonna be a little tricky.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.52,0:36:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們路上說\NTell me on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.66,0:36:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  先生\NSir. Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.79,0:36:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我們票數可能不佔多數  -什麼\N- We might not have a majority. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.99,0:37:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,民主黨在挖牆腳\NThe Dems are poaching people.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.99,0:37:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唐納  普拉斯基  可能還有別人\NDonner, Pulaski. Maybe more.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.72,0:37:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投票通過修正案嗎\NVoting for the amendment?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.78,0:37:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,部分支持  其餘棄權  我還在查是誰\NSome. Others abstaining. I'm still trying to figure out who.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.41,0:37:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們得推遲  弄清到底是怎麼回事\NWe need to delay and figure out what the fuck's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.47,0:37:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,點名  離休會還有49小時\NQuorum call. There's 49 hours until the recess.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.26,0:37:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一小時叫一個人來\NWe call a name an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.47,0:37:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾文戴爾先生\NMr. Avendale?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.72,0:37:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.88,0:37:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  你坐了我的位置\NExcuse me. I do believe you're sitting in my chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.49,0:37:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,德魯裏先生  現在進行到哪裏了\NMr. Drewry, what is the order of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.92,0:37:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們正在點名  先生\NWe are in a quorum call, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.80,0:37:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你怎麼不點名呢\NThen why aren't you calling the roll?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.60,0:37:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在點名  先生  不著急\NWe are, sir. In a deliberate manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.21,0:37:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,速度快點吧\NLet's speed it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.04,0:37:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布朗先生\NMr. Brown?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.31,0:38:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.01,0:38:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,動作再快點\NMore expeditious than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.76,0:38:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-博爾先生  -到\N- Mr. Burr? - Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.99,0:38:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-坎特維爾女士  -到\N- Ms. Cantwell? - Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.38,0:38:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,西裏尼先生\NMr. Cerini?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.11,0:38:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到\NCheck.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.08,0:38:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,康維爾\NCornwall?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.86,0:38:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.41,0:38:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,科森先生\NMr. Colson?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.82,0:38:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,道斯特女士\NMs. Douster
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.68,0:38:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.55,0:38:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法定人數夠了  我們票數不夠\NThey have a quorum. We don't have the numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.20,0:38:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出去  讓我們的人都出去\NOut. Let's get all our people out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.76,0:38:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-達默爾先生  達令先生  -到\N- Mr. Demerell. Mr. Darling. - Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.38,0:38:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-達斯瓦尼先生  -到\N- Mr. Daswani. - Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.99,0:38:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-唐納先生  -再快點\N- Mr. Donner. - Faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.52,0:38:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,道本先生  德懷爾先生\NMr. Dobben, Mr. Dwyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.51,0:38:33.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-埃倫伯格  安格  艾瑞克森  -到\N- Erinburgh, Engel, Erikson. - Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.37,0:38:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,菲爾德  法瑞森  詹特裏\NFeld, Ferrison, Gentry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.34,0:38:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈斯先生\NMr. Haas.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.47,0:38:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-懷特豪斯先生  -到\N- Mr. Whitehouse. - Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.56,0:38:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,維克先生  懷登先生\NMr. Wicker. Mr. Wyden.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.63,0:38:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席先生  沒有達到法定人數\NMr. President, a quorum is not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.96,0:38:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席允許少數黨領袖  艾瑞克森先生發言\NThe chair recognizes the minority leader, Mr. Erikson.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.99,0:39:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席先生\NMr. President,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.29,0:39:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我提議命令警衛官\NI move to direct the sergeant at arms
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.23,0:39:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,強制缺席參議員到場\Nto compel the attendance of absent Senators;
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.00,0:39:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對於無故缺席的所有參議員\Nthat warrants for the arrests of all senators not sick nor excused
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.21,0:39:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請會議主席簽發逮捕令予以逮捕\Nbe issued under the signature of the presiding officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.55,0:39:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對動議進行表決  同意者說"贊成"\NThe question is on the motion. All those in favor say "Aye"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.31,0:39:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贊成\NAye.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.93,0:39:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反對者說"反對"\NAll those opposed, "Nay."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.31,0:39:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反對\NNay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.90,0:39:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同意者佔多數  動議通過\NThe ayes have it, and the motion is agreed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.70,0:39:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我命令警衛官\NThe sergeant of arms is hereby instructed
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.28,0:39:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,強制缺席參議員到場\Nto compel the attendance of absent senators.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.58,0:39:35.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回國會的感覺真好\NIt feels good to be back in Congress.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.78,0:39:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在民主黨人已經授予國會警察\NThe Democrats have now empowered the Capitol Police
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.06,0:39:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在必要時逮捕缺席參議員的權利\Nto arrest absent members if necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.82,0:39:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,共和黨參議員柯蒂斯·哈斯\NAccording to Republican Senator Curtis Haas,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.94,0:39:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,福利改革修正案的堅決反對者之一\None of the staunchest opponents of the entitlement amendment,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.00,0:39:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這樣說道  副總統正在\Nthe vice president is, quote,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.45,0:39:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"用暴政取代民主\N"Replacing democracy with tyranny.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.37,0:39:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已經將參議院變成了國會裏的極權國家"\NHe's transformed the Senate into a police state within the Capitol."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.02,0:39:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是\NBut --
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.46,0:39:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在想躲避媒體更難了\NIt'll be even harder to stay out of the news now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.46,0:40:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那為什麼還要一起接受採訪\NThen why the joint interview?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.87,0:40:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我又看了一遍南卡羅來納的採訪\NI watched the South Carolina one again.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.19,0:40:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,說服他們給了我一份拷貝\NConvinced them to make me a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.09,0:40:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常有感染力  給你\NIt's powerful. Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.14,0:40:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我猜你可能想留一份\NI thought you might want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.17,0:40:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,採訪中有一個瞬間  你用手幫他捋頭髮\NThere's a moment where you ran your fingers through his hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.83,0:40:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常親密  非常有人情味\NIt's intimate and human.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.89,0:40:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,單是那一個瞬間就足以讓我為你丈夫投票\NThat moment alone would've made me want to vote for your husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.81,0:40:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像這樣的小事  能給你幾個月的清淨\NSomething like that will buy you months of flying beneath the radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.67,0:40:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想讓誰來進行採訪\NAnd who do you have in mind to conduct the interview?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.32,0:40:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這代表我被錄用了嗎\NDoes this mean I have the job?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.47,0:40:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這代表你還沒出局\NIt means you still haven't been ruled out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.97,0:40:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就當是有進步了\NWell, I'll consider that progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.06,0:41:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這裏是民主黨議員的衣帽間  赫克特\NThis is the Democratic cloak room, Hector.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.66,0:41:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們的在另一邊\NYours is on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.01,0:41:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的詭計不會成功的\NWhat you're doing won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.60,0:41:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有可能會  所以你大老遠地跑過來了\NIt might. Which is why you made the long walk over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.29,0:41:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰水\NIce water?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.19,0:41:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的人正坐著各種交通工具趕過來\NI have my people in planes, trains, and automobiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.75,0:41:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只需要六票達到法定人數\NAll I need is six to make my quorum.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.13,0:41:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想想我有26票能幹什麼\NThink what I can do with 26 votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.09,0:41:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在我都有45票了\NAnd I've got 45.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.87,0:41:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的人再怎麼趕也沒這麼快吧\NYou won't be able to get your planes and trains back here fast enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.89,0:41:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我願賭一把\NI'll roll those dice.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.70,0:41:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,會議警衛官的工作做得非常好\NThe sergeant at arms is very good at his job.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.17,0:41:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這樣正可以讓柯蒂斯明白  究竟誰是老大\NAnd this is a perfect way to show Curtis who's in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.62,0:41:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我這是在幫你  赫克特\NI'm doing you a favor, Hector.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.45,0:41:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告訴我你想要什麼\NTell me what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.00,0:41:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直想要的東西  我們達成的協議\NWhat I've always wanted. The package we shook hands on.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.31,0:41:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然後我就把參議院還給你\NThen I'll give you your Senate back.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.13,0:41:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們不能自願回來嗎\NThey can't come back voluntarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.66,0:41:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,選六個演技最好的出來\NPick your six best actors.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.66,0:41:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不能妥協  赫克特\NWe can't give in, Hector.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.16,0:41:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你按黨派路線走  我們就不會落到這個境地\NWe wouldn't be in this situation had you towed the party line.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.27,0:41:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,門多薩先生到場\NMr. Mendoza is present.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.01,0:42:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,表示抗議\NUnder protest.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.57,0:42:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,康維爾女士到場\NMs. Cornwall is present.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.84,0:42:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,表示抗議\NUnder protest.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.41,0:42:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,厄爾曼先生到場  沃爾什先生到場\NMr. Ullman is present. Mr. Walsh is present.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.56,0:42:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,道斯特女士到場\NMs. Douster is present.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.76,0:42:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈斯先生到場\NAnd Mr. Haas is present.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.74,0:42:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席先生  法定人數已經夠了\NMr. President, a quorum is now present.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.87,0:42:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你通過修正案吧  我會阻撓主法案的通過\NYou can pass the amendment. I'll just filibuster the main bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.77,0:42:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  你不會的\NNo, you won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.91,0:42:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看我會不會\NWatch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.98,0:42:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,儘管我特別想看你憋兩天尿的樣子\NAs much as I'd like to see you hold your piss for two days,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.96,0:42:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我們已經和赫克特達成協議了\Nwe struck a deal with Hector.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.58,0:42:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,替代修正案通過\NThe passage of the substitute amendment
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.20,0:42:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主法案就也通過\Nconstitutes passage of the main bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.32,0:42:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這我並不知情\NI wasn't informed of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.60,0:42:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要多留意小字附條款  柯蒂斯\NPay attention to the fine print, Curtis.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.59,0:42:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這比協議本身重要的多\NIt's far more important than the selling price.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.46,0:42:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們開始吧\NLet's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.07,0:42:34.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在立刻點名投票\NI want an immediate call of the roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.30,0:42:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一秒鐘時間都不要浪費\NDon't let half a second pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.65,0:42:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是  先生\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.66,0:42:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法定人數已經夠了\NA quorum is present.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.21,0:42:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,關於採納HR 934號法案的\NThe question is on the adoption of the substitute
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.23,0:42:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,替代修正案\Namendment to HR 934.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.28,0:42:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贊成或是反對\NThe yeas and nays have been ordered,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.54,0:42:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,書記官將開始點名投票\Nand the clerk will call the roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.04,0:42:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾伯納先生\NMr. Abner?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.02,0:42:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贊成\NAye.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.62,0:42:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾文戴爾先生\NMr. Avendale?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.77,0:42:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贊成\NAye.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.32,0:42:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布朗先生\NMr. Brown?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.22,0:42:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想為HR 934號法案提出一項修正案\NI'd like to propose an amendment to HR 934
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.28,0:42:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈斯先生  請不要破壞秩序  點名投票已經開始\NMr. Haas, you are out of order. The roll call has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.69,0:42:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,書記官將會繼續進行點名投票\NThe clerk will continue to call the roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.53,0:42:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布朗先生  博爾先生\NMr. Brown? Mr. Burr?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.44,0:42:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贊成\NAye.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.16,0:42:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坎特維爾女士\NMs. Cantwell?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.97,0:42:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贊成\NAye.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.63,0:43:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,西裏尼先生\NMr. Cerini?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.29,0:43:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贊成\NAye.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.86,0:43:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蔡斯先生\NMr. Chess?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.75,0:43:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贊成\NAye.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.36,0:43:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,康維爾女士\NMs. Cornwall?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.26,0:43:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反對\NNay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.01,0:43:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,科森先生\NMr. Colson?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.28,0:44:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很高興你能來\NI'm glad you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.70,0:44:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊  我也是\NYeah. Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.54,0:44:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得怎麼樣\NWhat'd you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.97,0:44:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,音樂非常美妙\NThe music was really beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.51,0:44:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟你想的不一樣嗎\NNot what you expected?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.95,0:44:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不知道會是什麼樣\NI wasn't sure what to expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.30,0:44:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我叫麗薩\NI'm Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.12,0:44:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞秋  抱歉\NRachel. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.46,0:44:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒事  我們裏面有餅乾和蛋糕  如果你\NNo. We've got cookies and cake inside, if you...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.68,0:44:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我覺得我還是...\NI think I'm gonna...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.53,0:44:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想見見我的一些朋友\NIf you want to meet some of my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.30,0:44:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-行啊  好  -行嗎\N- Yeah. Okay. - Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.44,0:44:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-行  -走吧\N- Yeah. Yeah. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.35,0:44:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,該把"奇跡創造者"寫進你的簡歷  弗蘭克\NWe should add "Miracle worker" to your resume, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.70,0:44:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拉撒路的魔術倒是精彩\NLazarus makes for a good magic act,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.70,0:44:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}聖經故事:馬大和馬利亞的兄弟  死後4天耶穌使他復活
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.36,0:44:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果那混蛋當初沒死\Nbut life would have been a lot easier
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.74,0:44:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,日子會輕鬆得多\Nif the bastard hadn't died in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.72,0:44:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統本來要發脾氣  但我安撫住他了\NThe president wanted to go ballistic, but I calmed him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.13,0:45:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我說  別擔心  弗蘭克會解決問題的\NI said, "Don't worry. Frank'll pull this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.17,0:45:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是嗎  我不會責怪你兩面派  雷蒙德\NDid you? I don't blame you for being two-faced, Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.43,0:45:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是厲害的政治手腕  但不能被人發現\NIt's good politics, as long as you don't get caught at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.30,0:45:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗蘭克  如果你認為我\NNow, Frank, if you think that I --
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.60,0:45:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒關係  雷蒙德  主會原諒你  晚安\NIt's okay, Raymond. Jesus forgives you. Goodnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.62,0:45:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人嗎\NHello?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.58,0:45:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人嗎\NHello?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.58,0:45:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想來點酒嗎\NCare for some wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.59,0:45:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用了\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.84,0:45:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,進來點\NStep in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.44,0:46:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,近一點  再近一點\NCloser. Closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.41,0:46:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,說一下你的名字和日期\NState your name and the date.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.77,0:46:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等等  為什麼...\NWait, why? I --
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.49,0:46:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請說一下你的名字和日期\NState your name and the date, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.68,0:46:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盧卡斯·古德溫  2月13日\NLucas Goodwin. February 13th.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.16,0:46:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,年份\NYear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.82,0:46:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2014年\N2014.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.68,0:46:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你現在或曾經在\NAre you currently or have you ever been a member of the --
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.13,0:46:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是幹什麼\NWhat -- what -- what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.83,0:46:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你現在或曾經在\NAre you currently or have you ever been a member
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.41,0:46:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,執法機構工作過嗎\Nof any law enforcement agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.42,0:46:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已經告訴過你我沒有了\NI already told you I wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.71,0:46:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,兩步驗證\NTwo-step verification.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.88,0:46:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  我沒有  以前也沒有\NNo, I'm not. And I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.92,0:46:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你現在或曾經向執法機構\NAre you currently or have you ever been
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.10,0:46:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提供過情報嗎\Nan informant for law enforcement?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.49,0:46:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.17,0:46:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得自己被跟蹤了嗎\NYou think you might have been followed?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.27,0:46:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,過去幾周發生過什麼奇怪的事嗎\NAnything strange the past few weeks?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.63,0:46:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這個...你知道嗎\NTh-- this is -- you know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.49,0:46:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這讓我很不舒服\NThis is making me feel uncomfortable --
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.33,0:46:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不是鬧著玩的\NWe're not fucking around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.27,0:46:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你認為聯調局沒查過你的郵件\NIf you think the FBI hasn't been tracking your posts,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.33,0:46:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你就太天真了\Nthen you're naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.93,0:46:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得他們知道我的身份嗎\NYou think they know who I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.04,0:46:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知道  你隱藏得很好\NNo. You hid yourself well.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.78,0:46:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要對《先驅報》做什麼\NWhat are you going to do with the Herald.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.99,0:46:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不做什麼\NNothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.86,0:46:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你為什麼想要訪問權限\NThen why did you want access?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.30,0:46:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已經有訪問權限了\NI already had access.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.49,0:46:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就是這樣聯繫你的\NIt's how I contacted you in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.03,0:47:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是想知道你是不是來真的\NJust needed to know if you were serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.45,0:47:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是腰果\NThat's Cashew.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.62,0:47:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你為什麼要聯繫我\NWhy did you contact me?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.78,0:47:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為你走投無路了\NBecause you're desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.88,0:47:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且我不喜歡當權者\NAnd I'm not fond of authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.02,0:47:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天  在安德伍德副總統的主持下\NJust today, under the leadership of Vice President Underwood,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.79,0:47:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,參議院通過了HR 934號法案\Nthe Senate passed HR 934,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.00,0:47:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同時通過了一個歷史性的福利改革修正案\Nalong with an historic entitlement reform amendment.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.24,0:47:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通過將正常退休和提早退休的年齡\NBy raising the retirement age to 68 and 65
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.09,0:47:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,分別提高到68和65歲\Nfor normal and early retirement, respectively,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.22,0:47:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們將確保未來幾代人的福利得到保障\Nwe will ensure entitlements for generations to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.08,0:47:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幾周後  等眾議院通過這項法案\NAnd when the House passes that bill in a few weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.29,0:47:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對此我完全有信心\Nas I fully expect it to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.27,0:48:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們就能結束政府的開銷凍結\Nwe will put the government freeze to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.80,0:48:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們將繼續為我們的國家服務\NWe will continue the business of serving our country,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.28,0:48:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不是讓國家癱瘓\Nrather than paralyzing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.64,0:48:11.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是美國人民應得的\NThe American people deserve no less.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.34,0:48:14.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們站在民主的聖壇上\NWe stand at the altar of democracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.17,0:48:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓我們站在一起\NLet us stand together.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.81,0:48:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟傑姬談過  我會在眾議院支持你\NI spoke to Jackie. You have my support in the House.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.74,0:48:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但現在眾議院還沒通過呢\NBut it hasn't passed the House yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.89,0:48:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在交給總統前  還長路漫漫\NThere's a long march before it arrives on the president's desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.63,0:48:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至於我  我以前總在鏡頭邊緣\NAs for me, I used to be on the edge of the frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.44,0:48:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在只有三英尺遠了\NNow I'm only three feet away.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.63,0:49:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}一個議案先在參議院表決  然後在眾議院表決\N眾議院表決時  可以自己起草一個版本\N也可以直接拿參議院的版本進行投票\N本集中弗蘭克想讓眾議院直接拿參議院通過的版本進行表決\N這樣更高效  如果有兩個版本\N雙方還得把兩個版本綜合在一起\N各自再投票一次  然後才能給總統簽字  生效成為法律
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.63,0:49:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}美國憲法規定副總統是參議院的主席\N但是平時副總統不干預參議院事務\N只有在投票出現平局或大的會議時才出席\N而本集中弗蘭克打破了常規  利用規則主持參議院投票\N所以才會對多數黨領袖說"把參議院還給你"
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.63,0:49:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}2013年9月  德克薩斯州茶黨參議員泰德·科魯茲\N鼓動同僚反對奧巴馬醫保法案\N要求國會預算法案同醫保法案落實掛鉤\N9月24日至25日  泰德·科魯茲連續在參議院發言21小時19分鐘\N為茶黨造出極大聲勢\N由於科魯茲等國會兩院中的茶黨成員在預算問題上堅持強硬立場\N而總統奧巴馬為了搞臭共和黨的名聲也拒絕談判\N美國聯邦政府於10月1日被迫"停擺"  關張大吉\N停擺持續了16天  兩黨在聲望均遭到極大打擊的情況下\N不得不坐在一起  達成預算協議
